<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3012] if you use setNorm, lucene writes a headerless separate norms file</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3012</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;In this case SR.reWrite just writes the bytes with no header...&lt;br/&gt;
we should write it always.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we can detect in these cases (segment written &amp;lt;= 3.1) with a &lt;br/&gt;
sketchy length == maxDoc check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12503327">LUCENE-3012</key>
            <summary>if you use setNorm, lucene writes a headerless separate norms file</summary>
