                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="13015676" author="rcmuir" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2011 00:29:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;changing fix version to 3.2, especially given &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3014&quot; title=&quot;comparator API for segment versions&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3014&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13035402" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 18 May 2011 15:16:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch (against branch_3x for simplicity) that uses the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3014&quot; title=&quot;comparator API for segment versions&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3014&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; comparator API.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because separate norms files are independent of the version that created the segment (e.g. one can call setNorm with 3.6 for a 3.1 segment), I think its really important that we fix this in 3.2 to write the header.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are no objections, I&apos;d like to commit, and then regenerate the tentative 3.2 indexes for trunk&apos;s TestBackwardsCompatibility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s no need to change the fileformats.html documentation, as what we are doing now is actually inconsistent with it, thus the bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13035459" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 18 May 2011 16:56:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree this is important to fix!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13035556" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 18 May 2011 19:31:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1124366, 1124369&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
